result.execSummary:
The defendant Tyri D. Webster was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Tyri D. Webster is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Tyri D. Webster was found guilty of Armed Robbery [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.32(2).
  • Tyri D. Webster was found guilty of Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: If probation or extended supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.  This applies to all counts and financial obligations.

Obey all of the rules and regulations of supervising probation agent.  
*  Pay supervision fees.  
Do not possess or consume alcoholic beverages and do not have alcoholic beverages within the residence.  Do not possess or consume controlled substances, except by prescription.  Do not be in taverns or on any premises licensed for the sale of intoxicating beverages, except restaurants or grocery stores.  Submit voluntarily to random tests of blood, breath or urine.  Participate in counseling deemed appropriate by agent.  Actively search for employment, be employed or attend an educational institution or vocational training program.  
*  Pay all court costs including all applicable surcharges.  
*  Court costs on Ct. 3 to be paid during extended supervision.   
*  Submit to a DNA sample (unless previously provided)  and pay surcharge.  
*  If unpaid financial obligations remain at discharge or revocation, civil judgment to be entered.  
*  Pay restitution in the sum of $200   plus surcharges - stipulated to.    
May not associate with gangs/gang members or gang affiliations.  May not have contact with Matthew B, Brendon M, Demetry L or Andrew  , unless otherwise permitted by the court/agent.   May not possess any weapons, including firearms.  No contact with any known felons.
